" --- SPC ] / SPC [ — next / prev navigation ------------------------------------------------------
" ideavimrc used ]c [c ]d [d ]e [e in NORMAL; multi-key NORMAL sequences don't
" exist here ([ ] are meow's beginning/end-of-thing), so they live on the
" keypad instead.
desc <leader>] next (change / diff / error)
map <leader>]c <action>(workbench.action.editor.nextChange)
map <leader>]d <action>(workbench.action.compareEditor.nextChange)
map <leader>]e <action>(editor.action.marker.nextInFiles)
desc <leader>[ previous (change / diff / error)
map <leader>[c <action>(workbench.action.editor.previousChange)
map <leader>[d <action>(workbench.action.compareEditor.previousChange)
map <leader>[e <action>(editor.action.marker.prevInFiles)

" ============================================================================
" NOT ported from .ideavimrc / .ideameowrc, and why
" ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
" * the whole meow-emulation section — the extension implements real meow;
"   the layout block at the top of this file is the native keymap itself.
" * set clipboard/ideajoin/number/relativenumber — IdeaVim/vim options; the
"   editor and the extension handle these themselves. Any such lines are
"   ignored if pasted, so copying an .ideavimrc or .ideameowrc wholesale is
"   safe.
" * <A-m> leader alias, C-key routing — only printable keys reach the meow
"   engine; use VS Code's keybindings.json for modifier chords.
" * SPC / (comment) and SPC ? — reserved by the keypad for describe-key and
"   the cheatsheet. Comment-line is on the editor's usual Ctrl-/ chord.
" * IntelliJ-only actions with no VS Code analog (tool windows like Maven /
"   Gradle / Coverage / Bookmarks / Hierarchy, GotoTest, ExtractInterface as
"   a distinct action, PasteMultiple history, Unwrap, presentation-assistant
"   overlays beyond screencast mode) — dropped rather than bound to the
"   wrong thing; editor.action.refactor covers the whole introduce/extract
"   family in VS Code.
" * :tabm / :delmarks / :set number! ex-commands — no ex layer here.
" * SPC <CR> (intentions): Enter can't be a keypad key; use Ctrl-. (quick
"   fix) or SPC s I (editor.action.quickFix).
" ============================================================================
